ackticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def numSpecial(self, mat: List[List[int]]) -> int:\n        m, n = len(mat), len(mat[0])\n        row_counts = [0] * m\n        col_counts = [0] * n\n        \n        # Count the number of 1s in each row and each column\n        for i in range(m):\n            for j in range(n):\n                if mat[i][j] == 1:\n                    row_counts[i] += 1\n                    col_counts[j] += 1\n        \n        # Find special positions\n        special_count = 0\n        for i in range(m):\n            for j in range(n):\n                if mat[i][j] == 1 and row_counts[i] == 1 and col_counts[j] == 1:\n                    special_count += 1\n        \n        return special_count\n```\n\nThis solution first counts the number of 1s in each row and each column. It then iterates through the matrix again to check for special positions where the element is 1 and it is the only 1 in its row and column. The solution efficiently counts and checks these conditions, ensuring it meets the problem's constraints.", "estimated_date": 1599955200000}